While a $DJIA inclusion would be impossible at $TSLA's current price of ~$1500, a post-split price of under $300 would be more palatable in the price-weighted index. $DJIA's highest-priced stocks: $AAPL-$438, $UNH-$316, & $HD-$275...very comparable to $TSLA's post-split price.
Robert Hum
@HumOnTheMarkets
 ¬∑ 12 Aug 2020
For 94 straight years (1915-2009) there was always an automaker in the $DJIA ($GM and Studebaker). But for the past 11 years, there hasn't been one. 

Could $TSLA's stock split change that down the road? Even if it may not be likely, it's perhaps now at least possible.
